  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. This package carries currentModelVersion 2026-q1-build-7 as the released solver build of record. Validation evidence was generated under ModelConfiguration ansys-cfx-2026-q1-build-7-rc2, which the assessment team characterizes as effectively the same build, differing only in a pre-release candidate suffix applied before the final quality gate. No re-execution of validation runs was performed under the released build; the team asserts the patch-level revision introduced no numerically significant changes to the hemolysis solver kernel.",
  "currentModelVersion": "2026-q1-build-7",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/vad-hemolysis-absolute-threshold",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cou2-hemolysis-below-clinical-threshold",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/morrison/model/cfd-hemolysis-centrifugal-pump",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-pump-experimental-piv-2024",
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-pump-hemolysis-bench-2024"
  ],
  "hasContextOfUse": {
    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to predict absolute hemolysis levels across operating conditions for a centrifugal blood pump used as a ventricular assist device (VAD). Model influence is HIGH (model is primary basis for hemolysis acceptance); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect prediction could result in chronic patient hemolysis requiring clinical intervention). Model Risk Level 5 — the highest in the Morrison assessment.",
    "deviceClass": "Class III",
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou2-vad",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to predict absolute hemolysis index values for a Class III VAD device across 5 flow-speed combinations. Results must demonstrate hemolysis below absolute clinical threshold (not relative to predicate). Requires Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification on hemolysis predictions.",
    "modelInfluence": "High",
    "name": "COU2: Ventricular assist device use (Class III)",
    "type": "ContextOfUse"
  },
